726293f-a.title: Queens: Calamus Avenue - Ankener Avenue
726293f-a.text:
Calamus Ave., at the S.W. corner of Ankener Ave. (left fore-
ground), showing the original Rapelje farmhouse, farm and outbuildings.
This is a set of four views,viewed westward.
January 1923.
Views 8 3 3: March 1923.
View 4: May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726292f-b.title: Queens: Calamus Avenue - Ankener Avenue
726292f-b.text:
Calamus Ave., west from Ankener Ave., showing in the foreoround
the Rapelje farmhouse and outbuildings. Note the winding turns of
Calamus Ave. In the background is the elevated structure, at about
47th Street, of the New York Connecting Railroad. This is a set of
three views.
January 1923.
View 2: January 1924.
View 3: September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster.

726294f-a.title: Queens: Calamus Avenue - Ankener Avenue
726294f-a.text:
Calamus Ave. (across front of peaked roof house in foreground),
between Ankener Ave. (riht) and Elks Road (left), showing in the
foreground the Rapelye farmhouse. Across from it are two homes,
Nos. 7481 and 7d42 Calamus Ave. This is a set of four views, showing
also general views northwest with Queens Boulevard in the background.
January 1924.
